The final thing that we have to do is set the proper line heights.

00:18:26.785 --> 00:18:28.315
Now, to do that,

00:18:28.315 --> 00:18:32.695
we're going to be working with the eight point grid system.

00:18:32.695 --> 00:18:35.890
Let me tell you a little bit about this.

00:18:35.890 --> 00:18:42.355
There's a great article that I linked in the resources, P-D-F file.

00:18:42.355 --> 00:18:43.810
Go ahead and check that out.

00:18:43.810 --> 00:18:49.420
It really explains why it's beneficial to use the eight point grid system in web design.

00:18:49.420 --> 00:18:58.405
Essentially, what we're trying to do is achieve a consistent vertical rhythm.

00:18:58.405 --> 00:19:03.265
So any measurement or any distance,

00:19:03.265 --> 00:19:06.940
any margin or padding that we're going to apply,

00:19:06.940 --> 00:19:13.285
any height that we're going to apply to our elements should be a multiple of eight.

00:19:13.285 --> 00:19:19.885
That applies to the text elements as well.

00:19:19.885 --> 00:19:25.465
The font size doesn't necessarily have to be a multiple of eight.

00:19:25.465 --> 00:19:31.675
What matters is the line height is a multiple of eight because the line height

00:19:31.675 --> 00:19:38.665
dictates how tall the lines of text are and if there are multiples of eight,

00:19:38.665 --> 00:19:43.840
then everything is going to fall nicely on a baseline grid.

00:19:43.840 --> 00:19:48.370
I'm going to show you a little bit about that when we add

00:19:48.370 --> 00:19:54.280
more elements and we follow this eight point grid system.

00:19:54.280 --> 00:19:58.915
But for now what you should know is that when it comes to typography,

00:19:58.915 --> 00:20:06.580
we're going to set the line height of the text elements to be a multiple of eight.

00:20:06.580 --> 00:20:09.055
Let's go ahead and do that right now.

